The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 A 28-year-old motorcyclist was killed and the pillion rider injured on Tuesday morning when their two-wheeler was hit by a speeding dumper truck on Eastern Metropolitan Bypass, off Parama island (Picture by Sanjoy Chattopadhyaya).

 aju Mollah was taken to a local hospital, where he later succumbed to his injuries. The pillion-rider, Habibul Molla, escaped with minor injuries. Police have impounded the killer truck, but the driver managed to flee.

 The Criminal Investigation Department (CID) arrested Kabir Hussain from Gopalnagar, in Bongaon, North 24-Parganas, in connection with a job racket that was busted recently. Sixty fake passports and Rs 30 lakh have been recovered from Hussain?s possession.

 ast Sunday, the CID had arrested three persons for the same racket ? Anshuman Gupta, Partha Mitra and Indranil Mitra ? following a tip-off. The three used to promise their ?clients? jobs in European countries.

 Basanti Das, 15, was found hanging from the ceiling of a room in the house where she worked in Rajpur, under Sonarpur police station, on Tuesday morning. 

 ccording to police, the domestic help was a native of Canning, on the city?s southern fringes. She used to work at the residence of a government officer. The body has been sent for post-mortem.

 The Muchipara police have started an inquiry into a theft of 304 g of gold items from a jewellery shop on Jagabandhu Lane, that came to light on Monday. 

 olice said a complaint by Mohar Ghosh, who works in the shop, said that the items, worth around Rs 2.1 lakh, were stolen on the night a former employee of the shop hailing from Bongaon, Kartick Das, had stayed on in the shop after meeting the shop-owner.

 Traffic in Howrah was disrupted for nearly an hour on Tuesday after supporters of Chhatra Parishad organised a roadblock at the Belgachhia crossing. The demonstrators were protesting the ?deteriorating? law and order situation in the town. 

 he agitation was withdrawn after senior police officers reached the spot and held out an assurance to look into the matter.

 Brindaban Karmakar and Subhas Halder were arrested in Halishahar, in North 24-Parganas, on Tuesday in connection with the theft of an antique idol. 

 ops had netted two persons when they were about to buy the piece from a dealer in Fancy Market. Investigations revealed the piece was stolen from Nanda Kishore Temple, in Halishahar, last year.

 A gang of armed men entered the house of Sadhana Basu, a CPM worker, in Belghoria on Monday night and took away valuables at gunpoint.

 A fire broke out in a factory at Mollar Gate, in Mahestala, on the southern fringes of the city, on Tuesday night. Ten fire tenders were pressed into service. The cause of fire is not known.

